A statement says Ngobeni tendered his resignation after discussions with Mayor Solly Msimanga and city manager Moeketsi Mosola. JOHANNESBURG - Tshwane Metro Police Department (TMPD) chief Steven Ngobeni has resigned, citing an &quot;irretrievable breakdown&quot; in his relationship with the city.A statement says Ngobeni tendered his resignation after discussions with Mayor Solly Msimanga and city manager Moeketsi Mosola.Msimanga had called for Ngobeni to step down after he was prevented from delivering his State of the Capital Address several weeks ago.Msimanga accused Tshwane metro police of not coming to his aid while a crowd disrupted proceedings. He later moved to another room to speak.Mayoral spokesperson Samkelo Mgobozi said, The police chief and the city have agreed on a separation. We ve appointed an acting police chief. 